ABUJA – The Federal Government has appointed Professor Anas Ahmad Sabir as the Chief Medical Director (CMD) of Usman Danfodiyo University Teaching Hospital (UDUTH) Sokoto. The Minister of Health Dr Osagie Emmanuel Ehanire disclosed this on Wednesday when he issued him his renewal letter in his office. The Minister in a statement made available to newsmen in Abuja by Director of Media&Publicity, FMOH A. A Chindaya congratulated Prof. Anas Sabir for his re-appointment and urged him to consolidate and improve upon his previous achievements to justify the confidence reposed in him. Osagie hinted that: ‘‘It is my expectation that you will continue to work collaboratively with all stakeholders to ensure that the hospital continues to deliver quality health care service to our people’’ The renewal of the appointment will take effect from May 17th, 2022. Meanwhile, in his acceptance speech, the Chief Medical Director, Usman Danfodiyo University Teaching Hospital Sokoto, Prof. Anas Ahmad Sabir thanked the Federal Government for his re-appointment and for giving him more opportunity to serve his fatherland. He added that the success he recorded during his first tenure is the support he derives from the Ministry and other stakeholders.